                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "How should a static method know the data within a instance ?\n\nAs you can see within the API and the manual getTranslation and all it's derevates are static methods.\nWhen you are not giving the locale, and are not setting a application locale, how should the static method know for which instance you want to have the locale ?\n\nThe correct handling is described within the manual and the API.\nThis is not a bug, this is correct OOP behaviour.",
